T* () Tj
T* (In such an environment, one would imagine that returns on private credit deals would have) Tj
T* (fallen to increasingly unappealing levels. That's what happened in the US where loose) Tj
T* (monetary conditions resulted in gobs of cash flooding into private credit, driving down) Tj
T* (returns and prompting fund managers to seek riskier deals in their search for yield.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (And yet, that's not the case in China.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Because credit is not flowing efficiently to all segments in China, experienced credit) Tj
T* (solution providers like ShoreVest can target far higher returns, and better downside) Tj
T* (protection, than those seen in more saturated markets.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Failing to Check Boxes) Tj
T* (China's banking system and bond markets have long failed to meet the needs of much of) Tj
T* (China's economy, due to how inefficiently that credit is allocated. Traditionally it was) Tj
T* (private sector companies that were locked out, forced to tap friends and family and later) Tj
T* (shadow banking institutions for funding at significantly higher interest rates than what) Tj
T* (banks provided state-owned firms. These days, although private sector companies can borrow) Tj
T* (from the banks, overinclusive credit-screening rules have resulted in a set of rigid boxes) Tj
T* (to check that still severely limit access.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (One example is the “social credit” system. China first started building its social credit) Tj
T* (system in 2014, but it was only in 2021 that implementation shifted from localized testing) Tj
T* (toward widespread enforcement. The system is mostly used to enforce legal judgements and) Tj
T* (corporate regulations rather than policing everyday morality, which is how it's often) Tj
T* (portrayed in the international media.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (People who fall foul of the system may face restrictions on luxury spending or be banned) Tj
T* (from purchasing high-speed train or plane tickets. Or they may find that firms they're) Tj
T* (affiliated with can no longer borrow from banks.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Even outside of the social credit strictures, China's banking system is highly bureaucratic,) Tj
T* (and bankers are acutely sensitive to allocating credit in ways that might run afoul of a) Tj
T* (strict interpretation of regulations. Consequently, they err on the side of caution, even if) Tj
T* (their decisions cause them to miss out on lending to certain successful and financially) Tj
T* (sound businesses. Such firms often have robust cash flow and ample assets to offer as) Tj
T* (security, making them ideal candidates for ShoreVest's private credit activities.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (The Credit Solution Opportunity) Tj
T* (The current private credit opportunity lies in providing credit solutions to quality private) Tj
T* (sector firms that have fallen victim to overinclusive credit-screening regulations.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Such was the experience of one ShoreVest client, a successful supplier of water purifiers to) Tj
T* (Chinese hotels and schools \(Company A\). While Company A had no creditworthiness issues, and) Tj
T* (was highly profitable, its founder invested in another unrelated company \(Company B\), which) Tj
T* (had taken out three loans he personally guaranteed, and which later defaulted. Because) Tj
T* (Company A’s founder was a personal guarantor on Company B’s nonperforming loans, this) Tj
T* (triggered an effective cross-default and Company A could no longer borrow. That's when) Tj
T* (ShoreVest stepped in, providing bridge loans and helping the founder get off the credit) Tj
T* (blacklist. Although ShoreVest charged a high cost of capital, our involvement solved Company) Tj
