T* () Tj
T* (ShoreVest is exposed to a steady flow of such opportunities, but private credit in China is) Tj
T* (a chronically underserved space.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Over the past decade, foreign private credit and distressed debt investors have mostly left) Tj
T* (China. To the extent they seek China exposure, it's mostly limited to Hong Kong.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Meanwhile, domestic sources of Chinese private credit collapsed in 2017 when Beijing) Tj
T* (launched its deleveraging campaign, resulting in shadow banking being scaled back to a) Tj
T* (fraction of its former size. By some measures, the gap left by shadow banking’s decline is) Tj
T* (about US$ 5 trillion in underserved space. But investors in private credit remain small in) Tj
T* (scale and fragmented.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Furthermore, private credit in China requires skills to structure deals, a network to source) Tj
T* (opportunities, and experience in navigating the nuances of China's economy. Few managers) Tj
T* (have all three. So, the paradox holds: China's cheapest credit and its highest returns) Tj
T* (coexist, not despite each other, but because of the barriers standing between them. This) Tj
T* (leaves ShoreVest relatively unchallenged in a lucrative corner of China's financial system.) Tj
